.TH "cgroup_attach_task" 9 "cgroup_attach_task" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
cgroup_attach_task \- attach a task or a whole threadgroup to a cgroup
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" cgroup_attach_task
.BI "(struct cgroup *dst_cgrp "  ","
.BI "struct task_struct *leader "  ","
.BI "bool threadgroup "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dst_cgrp" 12
the cgroup to attach to
.IP "leader" 12
the task or the leader of the threadgroup to be attached
.IP "threadgroup" 12
attach the whole threadgroup?
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Call holding cgroup_mutex and cgroup_threadgroup_rwsem.
